T1  - Commitment to Employer and Union: Effects of Membership Status
AU  - Conlon, Edward J.
AU  - Gallagher, Daniel G.
Y1  - 1987/03/01
PY  - 1987
DA  - 1987/03/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/255901
DO  - 10.5465/255901
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 151
EP  - 162
VL  - 30
IS  - 1
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - The article discusses the loyalty of employees to their employers and to labor unions. According to the author, prior research into this matter fails to consider whether or not union membership is voluntary, as well as the varying levels of union commitment. The author notes that this study examines the level of employee commitment to a union, the level of commitment to an employer and the correlation of these two measures across three identified subgroups: union members, nonmembers who have never been members and nonmembers who have left the union.
AB  - The article discusses the loyalty of employees to their employers and to labor unions. According to the author, prior research into this matter fails to consider whether or not union membership is voluntary, as well as the varying levels of union commitment. The author notes that this study examines the level of employee commitment to a union, the level of commitment to an employer and the correlation of these two measures across three identified subgroups: union members, nonmembers who have never been members and nonmembers who have left the union.
